HB 629 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Lyons
Abstract: Creates the "Krewe of Athena" motor vehicle special prestige license plate.
Provides for the creation, issuance, design, fees, implementation, distribution, and
rule promulgation applicable to this license plate.
Proposed law requires the Dept. of Public Safety and Corrections (DPS&C), office of motor
vehicles (OMV), to issue a special prestige license plate to be known as the "Krewe of
Athena" license plate, provided there is a minimum of 1,000 applicants for such a plate.
Proposed law requires that the secretary work in conjunction with the Krewe of Athena
Carnival Club, Inc. to select the color and design of the plate. Requires the design include
the words "Krewe of Athena".
Proposed law specifies that the license plates will be issued, upon application, to any citizen
of La. in the same manner as any other motor vehicle license plate. Further directs the
DPS&C, OMV, to create the special prestige plate when the applicable statutory provisions
